I got the following Verilog module with the parameter `REGS`:

```verilog
module RegisterFile
#(
    parameter REGS /*verilator public*/ = 1
)
(
    input clk_i,
    input reset_n_i
);
    reg[0:31] r0;

    always @(posedge clk_i, negedge reset_n_i) begin
        if(reset_n_i == 1'b0)
            r0 <= 0;
		else
            r0 <= REGS;
    end
endmodule
```

Now I would like to set this parameter in my Verilator C++/SystemC code when instantiating the module:

```cpp
#include "VRegisterFile.h"

int sc_main(int argc, char** argv) {
    Verilated::commandArgs(argc, argv);
    Verilated::traceEverOn(true);

    // input signals
    sc_clock clk{"clk", 2, SC_NS, 0.5, 0, SC_NS, true};
    sc_signal<bool> reset_n;

    // instantiate verilog module and connect signals
    // TODO set REGS <- how?
    VRegisterFile* register_file = new VRegisterFile{"register_file"};
    register_file->clk_i(clk);
    register_file->reset_n_i(reset_n);
}
```

I couldn't find anything in the docs or examples other than the `/*verilator public*/` comment to emit a parameter in C code.
